{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d5d33382-3a1a-4334-82af-ae7b4a9eabce","content":"You're on MSTest v3.8.2, which supports **constructor injection for `TestContext`** and the `IAsyncInitialization` / `IAsyncDisposable` patterns.\n\nHere's the recommended approach:\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\npublic class MyTests : IAsyncInitialization, IAsyncDisposable\n{\n    public TestContext TestContext { get; }\n\n    // Synchronous init via constructor (inject TestContext)\n    public MyTests(TestContext testContext)\n    {\n        TestContext = testContext;\n        // other sync setup here\n    }\n\n    // Async init — called automatically after construction\n    public async Task InitializeAsync()\n    {\n        // async setup (e.g., DB connections, HTTP clients)\n        await Task.CompletedTask;\n    }\n\n    // Async cleanup\n    public async ValueTask DisposeAsync()\n    {\n        // async teardown\n        await Task.CompletedTask;\n    }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public void ExampleTest()\n    {\n        TestContext.WriteLine(\"Running test!\");\n        Assert.IsTrue(true);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- **Constructor injection** — `TestContext` is passed via the constructor (MSTest v3+), replacing the old property-setter pattern.\n- **`IAsyncInitialization`** — implement `InitializeAsync()` for async setup; MSTest calls it automatically after construction.\n- **`IAsyncDisposable`** — implement `DisposeAsync()` for async teardown (replaces `[TestCleanup]` for async work).\n- These replace the older `[TestInitialize]` / `[TestCleanup]` attributes when you need constructor DI + async lifecycle.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"b4d5c34e-cae0-400c-8df3-69a64c63bdcb","outputTokens":417,"requestId":"A029:2A6123:6295DBA:6B24A84:6A034CD6"},"id":"a6956cda-8bc7-4fa0-8706-6d3dfcd0b233","timestamp":"2026-05-12T15:53:04.866Z","parentId":"d49a1ed8-e466-4f10-9a8f-fa13496deabe"}
